1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper proposes a joint beamforming algorithm for a multiuser wireless information and power transfer (MU-WIPT) system that maximizes the total harvested energy of energy harvesting (EH) users and guarantees the signal to interference plus noise ratio (SINR) constraints of the co-scheduled information decoding (ID) users. This involves optimizing the transmission of information and power, which falls under the purview of information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper deals with a wireless communication system that involves multiple users and the transmission of both information and power. This falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a joint beamforming algorithm that optimizes the transmission of information and power in a multiuser wireless system. This involves designing a control system that can maximize the total harvested energy of energy harvesting (EH) users and guarantee the SINR constraints of the co-scheduled information decoding (ID) users. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper deals with a wireless communication system that involves the transmission of both information and power. This can be considered a multimedia application, as it involves the transmission of different types of data.
